  "text": "High-fat, fructose and cholesterol (AMLN diet) [CITATION_1] Diet high in fat (40%, of which 18% is transfat), plus fructose (22%) and cholesterol (2%) administered for 30 weeks [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Another link between defects in liver and adipose tissue may be the enzyme dipeptidyl peptidase 4 (DPP-4), which can promote insulin resistance. Circulating DPP-4 is secreted by hepatocytes and acts in concert with plasma factor Xa to stimulate inflammatory macrophages within visceral adipose tissue in mice. This effect is known to promote insulin resistance, underscoring the important cross talk between liver and other tissues underlying metabolic dysregulation in NAFLD [CITATION_4] .",
